**Bug description**
1.0.0-M8 PRE Using ChatClient.Builder to build the client does not correctly identify the tools after adding defaultTools. Use the defaultToolCallbacks method to add the default tool to take effect

**Environment**
jdk 17, SpringBoot3.4.2, SpringAI 1.0.0-M8 PRE

**Steps to reproduce**
` @Bean
    public ChatClient createChatClient(ChatClient.Builder builder, ToolCallbackProvider tools, ChatMemory chatMemory) {

        ChatClient.Builder chatClientBuilder = builder.defaultTools(tools.getToolCallbacks())
                .defaultSystem("""
                        You are an AI assistant integrated into the system. Your task is to help users complete various tasks. Please call the registered tools to complete the tasks according to the different questions asked by the users. You can use the tools to obtain information, perform operations or provide suggestions. Please make sure to use the most appropriate tools to meet the needs of users when answering their questions.
                        """)
                .defaultAdvisors(MessageChatMemoryAdvisor.builder(chatMemory).build()
                );
        return chatClientBuilder.build();
    }`
